♪ What is this feeling ♪

02:35.709 --> 02:39.291
♪ You're so sure of? ♪

02:41.083 --> 02:42.625
He seemed pretty serious
to me.

02:42.625 --> 02:44.917
[Ian] For a meth head,
he ran fast.

02:44.917 --> 02:46.625
Fuckin' Monica,
fuckin' up our lives,

02:46.625 --> 02:47.750
- even in death.
- [Ian] Hey, shh.

02:47.750 --> 02:49.875
Don't let Fiona hear you.
She'll go ballistic.

02:49.875 --> 02:52.125
So, how scary was he?

02:52.125 --> 02:54.250
Was he big?
Was he armed?

02:54.250 --> 02:55.667
- [Debbie] Did he know my name?
- You know, 'cause we can

02:55.667 --> 02:56.041
be pretty fuckin' scary too
if we have to.

02:56.041 --> 02:57.667
Agreed.

02:57.667 --> 02:58.959
Meeting adjourned.

03:00.000 --> 03:02.875
"Meeting adjourned"?

03:02.875 --> 03:06.458
[Lip] You got some magical way
to get 70 grand in meth?

03:06.458 --> 03:09.083
I do not.
I simply don't wish

03:09.083 --> 03:10.917
to discuss it further.

03:10.917 --> 03:12.000
Are you high, Frank?

03:12.000 --> 03:14.125
[Frank] High on life.

03:14.125 --> 03:15.166
High on possibility.

03:15.166 --> 03:17.500
[Lip] You're the one
who stirred up

03:17.500 --> 03:18.792
all this shit
in the first place

03:18.792 --> 03:19.709
by robbing the storage unit.

03:19.709 --> 03:21.000
I keep telling you,
that's the old Frank.

03:21.000 --> 03:23.792
You're talking to
the new Frank.

03:23.792 --> 03:26.083
Or the young Frank.

03:26.083 --> 03:29.208
God, maybe it's not
even Frank.

03:29.208 --> 03:31.125
Maybe it's Francis now.

03:31.125 --> 03:32.709
[Ian] If you don't figure out
a way to help us out

03:32.709 --> 03:34.458
of this shit,
I'm gonna take a tire iron

03:34.458 --> 03:36.458
- to old Frank.
- You've been a drama queen

03:36.458 --> 03:37.667
since the day
you were born, Ian.

03:37.667 --> 03:41.709
Wouldn't stop screaming until
you were fully detoxed.

03:44.208 --> 03:46.583
This meth head doesn't know
where we live.

03:46.583 --> 03:49.750
We just have to stay away
from the storage unit

03:49.750 --> 03:52.125
and steer clear
of the cemetery.

03:52.125 --> 03:54.792
And if he does manage
to find his way here,

03:54.792 --> 03:58.208
we stick by our story.
The secret of what happened

03:58.208 --> 04:00.375
to his meth lies with Monica,

04:00.375 --> 04:01.333
God bless her rotting soul.

04:01.333 --> 04:05.000
- [floorboards creak]
- [Debbie] Shh!

04:05.000 --> 04:05.709
- [Fiona] Mornin'.
- [Liam] Morning.

04:05.709 --> 04:06.834
[Lip] Hey.

04:06.834 --> 04:09.875
♪ funk music ♪

04:09.875 --> 04:14.667
♪♪♪

04:14.667 --> 04:16.917
Well, you're here early,
Debs.

04:16.917 --> 04:18.750
Ah, yup.
Gotta go.

04:18.750 --> 04:19.917
Yeah, you know, me too.

04:19.917 --> 04:21.125
Yup.

04:21.125 --> 04:22.583
[Frank] Looking to the future

04:22.583 --> 04:25.166
is the order of the day, kids.

04:25.166 --> 04:28.750
No worrying about old news.

04:28.750 --> 04:30.500
What old news, Frank?

04:32.500 --> 04:34.250
I go by Francis now.

04:36.125 --> 04:38.000
Yevgeny never stops eating.

04:38.000 --> 04:40.250
The grocery bills
are ridiculous.

04:40.250 --> 04:43.792
Mortgage is past due,
tips at Patsy's are for shit.

04:43.792 --> 04:45.500
The Alibi is empty.
Makes me sick to say it,

04:45.500 --> 04:48.208
but I'm starting to regret
getting Svetlana arrested.

04:48.208 --> 04:51.208
Kevin, are you listening?

04:51.208 --> 04:53.041
What?
Yes.

04:53.041 --> 04:55.625
[sighs] Do we really have to
get these genetics tests?

04:55.625 --> 04:58.667
- They're expensive.
- Yes, we have to get 'em.

04:58.667 --> 04:59.917
What if I have the Bracka gene

04:59.917 --> 05:01.041
- and I gave it to one of 'em?
- Don't think you can get

05:01.041 --> 05:02.291
ovarian cancer, Kev.

05:02.291 --> 05:04.250
Well, we still have to
find out

05:04.250 --> 05:05.291
what my shitty orphan genes

05:05.291 --> 05:06.500
have in store for them.

05:06.500 --> 05:07.250
Don't want any more surprises.

05:07.250 --> 05:09.792
- [knocking]
- [Fiona] Hey.

05:09.792 --> 05:11.750
You guys still got those,
uh, cleaning products

05:11.750 --> 05:13.417
from the topless maid service?

05:13.417 --> 05:15.000
I gotta clean out
the empty unit.

05:15.000 --> 05:16.875
[Veronica]
Yeah, let me get 'em.

05:19.291 --> 05:21.625
Have you examined
your breasts

05:21.625 --> 05:22.583
in the shower
this morning, Fiona?

05:22.583 --> 05:25.208
[laughs] Good morning
to you too, Kev.

05:25.208 --> 05:27.250
A self exam is
no laughing matter.

05:27.250 --> 05:28.875
Do you even know how
to do it right?

05:28.875 --> 05:30.458
'Cause it's not just here.

05:30.458 --> 05:31.792
Let me show you.
Raise your arms.

05:31.792 --> 05:35.000
- [laughing] Are you serious?
- [Veronica] He won't stop

05:35.000 --> 05:36.959
until he shows you.
It's not a sex thing.

05:36.959 --> 05:38.250
It's a "save your life" thing.

05:38.250 --> 05:40.375
I thought
your lump was benign.

05:40.375 --> 05:42.166
My lump was benign,
but the scare was very, very--

05:42.166 --> 05:44.500
shit, what is the word again?

05:44.500 --> 05:46.291
- Malignant.
- [Kev] Malignant!

05:46.291 --> 05:48.000
Raise your arms, Fiona,
because "malignant"

05:48.000 --> 05:49.583
is not a word you ever want
to have to remember.

05:49.583 --> 05:51.709
Drop the overalls.

05:54.166 --> 05:56.458
All right.
It's not just here.

05:56.458 --> 05:58.625
It's here too,
and under the arms here.

05:58.625 --> 05:59.667
All right?

06:05.834 --> 06:06.834
I got it, thanks.

06:06.834 --> 06:08.458
Thank you.

06:08.458 --> 06:10.667
- [Fiona] Okay.
- All right, you're good.

06:10.667 --> 06:13.125
Okay.

06:13.125 --> 06:14.750
It's like having four toddlers.

06:14.750 --> 06:16.375
Most action I've gotten
in weeks.

06:16.375 --> 06:17.834
[chuckles]

06:17.834 --> 06:18.625
So, now there's a meth dealer

06:18.625 --> 06:21.166
coming out
of the fuckin' woodwork.

06:21.166 --> 06:22.917
[Brad] Hate to say
I told you so.

06:22.917 --> 06:23.709
Really?
'Cause I think you kind of

06:23.709 --> 06:25.667
- fucking love it.
- [chuckles]

06:25.667 --> 06:27.208
Love it more if
you listened to me.

06:27.208 --> 06:30.000
Ah, it's just so twisted.

06:30.000 --> 06:32.458
The meth dealer wanting
his stolen drugs back?

06:32.458 --> 06:34.208
That's what's twisted?

06:34.208 --> 06:36.542
That's what
our mother left us.

06:36.542 --> 06:38.375
- You know, stolen drugs.
- Yeah--yeah,

06:38.375 --> 06:39.500
that, I'll give you.

06:39.500 --> 06:42.834
I guess I just never
really saw that before.

06:42.834 --> 06:44.250
Sobriety goggles are
kind of like

06:44.250 --> 06:46.125
the opposite of beer goggles.

06:46.125 --> 06:48.125
Fucked-up shit stops
looking normal.

06:50.166 --> 06:52.792
Brad, ETA on the red Harley?

06:52.792 --> 06:54.166
End of the week.

06:54.166 --> 06:55.500
Brad says "end of the week,"

06:55.500 --> 06:56.542
so probably next Wednesday.

06:56.542 --> 06:59.542
[Lip] And fuckin' Charlie
and Sierra.

06:59.542 --> 07:01.834
I-I-I mean, I can't even
hang with Lucas anymore

07:01.834 --> 07:03.750
'cause...you know,
I can't see them

07:03.750 --> 07:06.250
or see her, just...

07:06.250 --> 07:10.333
...you know, clean or not,
the guy's a fucking prick.

07:10.333 --> 07:12.083
All right, and she wants
to be with him?

07:12.083 --> 07:14.917
I mean, it's...I don't know,
it's fucking depressing.

07:14.917 --> 07:16.625
[Brad]
You're not depressed, Lip.

07:16.625 --> 07:18.792
You're self-obsessed.

07:18.792 --> 07:19.792
Here.

07:19.792 --> 07:22.375
- The fuck is this?
- This is a piece of shit

07:22.375 --> 07:23.625
that you're gonna turn into
not-a-piece-of-shit.

07:28.917 --> 07:31.333
Oh, are you giving me
a project?

07:31.333 --> 07:32.709
I'm giving you something
to obsess about

07:32.709 --> 07:35.125
that isn't you.
Fix it up.

07:35.125 --> 07:37.917
Make it run, make it pretty.

07:37.917 --> 07:39.959
What's the point?

07:39.959 --> 07:41.458
The point is to get
your head out of your ass

07:41.458 --> 07:43.500
before you decide
to drink again

07:43.500 --> 07:45.250
and hit an even worse bottom.

07:50.417 --> 07:52.625
[jazz music plays on radio]

07:52.625 --> 07:54.291
[volume increases]

07:54.291 --> 07:56.166
♪♪♪

07:57.291 --> 07:59.041
♪♪♪

07:59.041 --> 08:01.417
[tires screeching]

08:01.417 --> 08:03.083
♪♪♪

08:03.083 --> 08:04.125
[tires screech]

08:04.125 --> 08:09.250
♪♪♪

08:11.959 --> 08:15.875
[crashing]

08:15.875 --> 08:20.750
♪♪♪

08:23.750 --> 08:25.875
[Blanca] Dios mio.

08:26.917 --> 08:29.834
Ah...

08:31.834 --> 08:34.917
Brought you that
chocolate-flavored soy shit

08:34.917 --> 08:36.583
you like to pretend is coffee.

08:36.583 --> 08:40.500
With a side of snark,
just like I like it.

08:40.500 --> 08:42.166
I thought you had work today.

08:42.166 --> 08:44.417
Soon, yeah.

08:45.500 --> 08:50.333
So, that drug dealer
that chased me?

08:50.333 --> 08:51.709
Can't seem to shake it off.

08:51.709 --> 08:53.166
I don't know what's wrong
with me.

08:53.166 --> 08:54.709
[chuckles softly]

08:54.709 --> 08:56.667
You laughing at me?

08:56.667 --> 08:59.125
Only because it's still hard
for me to tell

08:59.125 --> 09:00.834
when you're joking.
Are you serious?

09:01.709 --> 09:06.250
Um...well,
nothing's wrong with you.

09:06.250 --> 09:08.709
I think it's probably hard
for a normal human

09:08.709 --> 09:11.667
to shake off a drug dealer
chasing them.

09:11.667 --> 09:15.917
Well, Gallaghers are generally
not normal humans.

09:15.917 --> 09:17.500
Grief can change people.

09:19.125 --> 09:20.834
What?

09:20.834 --> 09:22.917
Um...grief.

09:22.917 --> 09:26.709
I mean, your mother died.
It changes you.

09:26.709 --> 09:30.917
Maybe you should
talk to the counselor.

09:30.917 --> 09:32.125
Rather talk to you.

09:32.125 --> 09:35.208
In fact, I'd...

09:35.208 --> 09:39.375
...rather do something with you
that doesn't involve talking.

09:39.375 --> 09:41.291
Ah.
Well, sorry.

09:41.291 --> 09:44.417
I am busy trying to help
at-risk youth.

09:50.375 --> 09:53.291
Fuck--oh, Jesus.

09:53.291 --> 09:54.709
- [Fiona] Hey.
- What is that?

09:54.709 --> 09:57.917
[sighs] Pretty sure
it's baby shit.

09:57.917 --> 09:59.417
- [sighs, groans]
- [Lip] The woman you evicted

09:59.417 --> 10:01.750
wiped baby shit everywhere?

10:01.750 --> 10:03.834
Yeah, parting gift.

10:03.834 --> 10:05.834
And I'm hoping it's baby shit.

10:05.834 --> 10:08.834
- [Lip] Right.
- [Fiona sighs]

10:08.834 --> 10:11.834
- "Slumlord twat."
- [Fiona] Yeah.

10:11.834 --> 10:12.667
Kind of a nice ring
to it, huh?

10:12.667 --> 10:15.458
- Yeah.
- [Fiona] So, you, uh--

10:15.458 --> 10:16.667
you here to tell me what

10:16.667 --> 10:17.959
your little family meeting

10:17.959 --> 10:18.959
was about this morning?

10:18.959 --> 10:20.542
I was gonna ask about
borrowing your car.

10:20.542 --> 10:23.041
I got a friend who's in trouble.

10:23.041 --> 10:25.208
- Oh, what kind of trouble?
- It's a DUI.

10:25.208 --> 10:26.959
Oh.
Right here.

10:26.959 --> 10:27.291
Great.
Thanks, Fi.

10:27.291 --> 10:29.875
Sure.

10:29.875 --> 10:31.583
Oh, hey, what time
are you coming back?

10:31.583 --> 10:33.583
[door slams]

10:33.583 --> 10:35.458
Hey.
[sniffs] Ugh.

10:35.458 --> 10:37.792
Brought you a latte
from my fancy new latte maker.

10:37.792 --> 10:40.792
- Ooh, thanks.
- [Nessa] Ugh.

10:40.792 --> 10:43.250
You weren't kidding
about this place.

10:43.250 --> 10:44.917
Ugh. [sniffs]

10:44.917 --> 10:46.125
So, did you find a renter yet?

10:46.125 --> 10:47.583
No.

10:47.583 --> 10:51.375
I did spend $140
on credit checks.

10:51.375 --> 10:53.583
Turns out that nice clothes
and the appearance of money

10:53.583 --> 10:57.542
do not make for great credit.

10:57.542 --> 10:59.291
Why are you drawing
on the walls?

10:59.291 --> 11:01.166
'Cause I'd rather
my one good applicant

11:01.166 --> 11:02.458
not read the words
"thunder cunt."

11:02.458 --> 11:05.125
- [Nessa laughs]
- Guy insisted

11:05.125 --> 11:05.917
on seeing the place today,
and I don't have time

11:05.917 --> 11:09.500
to paint before
he gets here.

11:09.500 --> 11:12.417
[Mel] Hey, good news.
Charlotte and Trotter--

11:12.417 --> 11:14.000
from the gym?
They wanna move in here.

11:14.000 --> 11:15.875
[sniffing]

11:15.875 --> 11:18.125
Wha...what is that smell?

11:18.125 --> 11:19.166
It's human feces.

11:19.166 --> 11:22.000
Do we like Charlotte
and Trotter from the gym?

11:22.000 --> 11:25.750
Charlotte's cool.
Trotter's a bit of a shit-show.

11:25.750 --> 11:28.208
So, you'd rather live
next to some stranger

11:28.208 --> 11:31.250
that your new
sidepiece picks out?

11:31.250 --> 11:33.750
Can your friends pass
a credit check?

11:33.750 --> 11:35.667
They're cool.

11:35.667 --> 11:37.709
And we pay our rent on time
and we vouch for them.

11:37.709 --> 11:41.250
I still have to run the report.
And I have to meet them.

11:41.250 --> 11:42.834
Fine.
I'll set it up.

11:47.667 --> 11:51.250
My girlfriend's kind of
a thunder cunt.

11:51.250 --> 11:53.083
- Not just kind of.
- [laughs]

11:53.083 --> 11:54.417
It's the fertility hormones.

11:54.417 --> 11:56.458
- Is it?
- [Nessa laughs]

11:56.458 --> 11:59.542
♪ lively party music ♪

11:59.542 --> 12:04.667
♪♪♪

12:12.750 --> 12:13.917
What up?

12:13.917 --> 12:15.792
[Carl]
What up, what up?

12:15.792 --> 12:18.792
How are you guys doing?
Come on, bring it in.

12:27.792 --> 12:28.875
Jesus.

12:30.083 --> 12:33.917
Aye--what the fuck happened?

12:33.917 --> 12:35.750
I drove into a house.

12:35.750 --> 12:36.834
Serious?

12:36.834 --> 12:37.875
Yeah.

12:39.959 --> 12:41.458
You kill anybody?

12:41.458 --> 12:43.250
By the grace of a god
I don't believe in,

12:43.250 --> 12:46.125
the only thing I destroyed
was my own life...

12:46.125 --> 12:48.750
...and the house itself.

12:48.750 --> 12:50.709
- Are you in pain?
- [Youens] Both physical

12:50.709 --> 12:52.208
and existential.

12:52.208 --> 12:53.083
We'll stop by the drugstore,

12:53.083 --> 12:54.750
see what they got
for existential pain.

12:54.750 --> 12:57.291
Probably something
over the counter.

13:13.834 --> 13:14.917
Watch your head.

13:14.917 --> 13:15.792
Ugh.

13:23.333 --> 13:25.000
Hey, Frank?
Some kid knocked over

13:25.000 --> 13:26.667
- a bunch of orchids--
- It's Francis.

13:26.667 --> 13:28.083
What?

13:28.083 --> 13:31.125
My name.
I made a new tag this morning.

13:31.125 --> 13:33.458
Did you know that
the name Francis means

13:33.458 --> 13:35.750
"comes from France,"
which is a little galling,

13:35.750 --> 13:37.375
because the French use
too much butter

13:37.375 --> 13:38.041
in their cooking
and they refuse

13:38.041 --> 13:39.959
to pronounce the letter H.

13:39.959 --> 13:42.125
But the name Francis
is more commonly used

13:42.125 --> 13:44.583
to refer to Saint Francis
of Assisi.

13:44.583 --> 13:45.959
Listen to this:
"Francis was designated

13:45.959 --> 13:48.875
patron saint of Italy.
He later became associated

13:48.875 --> 13:51.792
with the patronage
of animals,

13:51.792 --> 13:53.375
and it became customary

13:53.375 --> 13:55.083
to hold ceremonies
blessing animals

13:55.083 --> 13:58.041
